1
00:00:00,299 --> 00:00:02,472
Let's run it again, everyone.

2
00:00:17,982 --> 00:00:20,222
Hey, Dr. Ashura.

3
00:00:23,709 --> 00:00:27,675
Oh, the usual ice cream.

4
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:29,593
Thanks.

5
00:00:29,853 --> 00:00:34,903
The thing is, my stomach's been hurting
since last night.

6
00:00:35,272 --> 00:00:36,872
It hurts a lot.

7
00:00:37,032 --> 00:00:38,612
Did you eat something bad?

8
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:40,780
Probably the bread.

9
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:42,520
It was a little moldy, but...

10
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,739
Open your mouth.

11
00:00:47,807 --> 00:00:49,326
Ow! What're you doing?!

12
00:00:49,326 --> 00:00:51,360
- Poor skin turgor.
- Tur... what?

13
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:53,333
When I pinch your skin,
it doesn't spring back.

14
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:56,700
Your mouth is dry, too. You're dehydrated.
We're going to the hospital now.

15
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,840
- C'mon, that's overblown.
- We're going. Now.

16
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:02,660
Can't you just gimme some medicine? Huh?

17
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:06,180
Bit of an overreaction, right?

18
00:01:08,780 --> 00:01:10,140
I brought a patient.

19
00:01:10,340 --> 00:01:11,573
Tatsu!

20
00:01:11,606 --> 00:01:13,716
Hey, you all look good!

21
00:01:13,716 --> 00:01:15,440
Tatsu, long time no see.

22
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:18,520
Dr. Daikoku, did you get through
that divorce crisis?

23
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,319
Ah, yeah, somehow.

24
00:01:20,319 --> 00:01:21,525
Oh, good.

25
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:23,893
What brings you in today?

26
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:27,180
Food poisoning this time.

27
00:01:27,635 --> 00:01:28,840
Get his vital signs first.

28
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,190
Tatsu, right this way.

29
00:01:30,332 --> 00:01:31,615
Vital signs?

30
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,530
Please sit down.

31
00:01:34,146 --> 00:01:35,263
Sit?

32
00:01:35,263 --> 00:01:37,056
- I'll take your jacket.
- Sure.

33
00:01:38,027 --> 00:01:40,549
- Take good care of it.
- Okay.

34
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:46,560
Dr. Anno, BP 98 over 60,
pulse in the 80s, O2 saturation normal.

35
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:49,640
Vital signs are stable.
Clean him up first, then start fluids.

36
00:01:49,706 --> 00:01:50,913
Understood.

37
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:53,360
Tatsu, let's get you to the shower.

38
00:01:53,693 --> 00:01:55,180
Huh? A bath?

39
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,400
Yes.

40
00:01:56,453 --> 00:01:58,720
- You gonna wash me?
- Wash yourself, please.

41
00:01:58,780 --> 00:02:00,093
Aw, come on.

42
00:02:00,093 --> 00:02:02,906
Taishaku General Hospital

43
00:02:11,330 --> 00:02:16,610
Mr. Konishi, you did a great job.
You look like a different person.

44
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,576
I'm a good-looking guy, right?

45
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:23,450
Dr. Anno, the blood work is back.

46
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:27,436
BUN and creatinine are elevated.

47
00:02:28,330 --> 00:02:30,410
Doc, am I gonna be okay?

48
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:32,110
We'll admit you for observation.

49
00:02:32,116 --> 00:02:33,452
Observation?

50
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,630
Seriously?

51
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:42,970
That was my first time treating
a homeless patient.

52
00:02:43,470 --> 00:02:47,430
Tatsu lives in the park nearby.
He comes in all the time.

53
00:02:47,830 --> 00:02:51,476
Last winter, he was admitted for the flu.

54
00:02:51,476 --> 00:02:52,896
He's a regular here.

55
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:58,170
He seems nice, but there's no way
he can pay for treatment.

56
00:02:58,236 --> 00:03:02,523
True. But if he needs treatment,
we can't turn him away.

57
00:03:02,523 --> 00:03:03,803
Right.

58
00:03:04,290 --> 00:03:09,403
The Medical Practitioners Act says we can't
refuse treatment based on the ability to pay.

59
00:03:11,383 --> 00:03:14,610
You seemed pretty friendly
with Tatsu, Dr. Anno.

60
00:03:18,402 --> 00:03:19,603
Incoming.

61
00:03:21,783 --> 00:03:23,410
Kenta Sato, age 28.

62
00:03:23,410 --> 00:03:26,790
His fiancée found him collapsed at home
and called for an ambulance.

63
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:28,226
One, two, three!

64
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:36,050
Mr. Sato, can you hear me?
Can you understand me?

65
00:03:36,076 --> 00:03:38,183
His consciousness level is
significantly reduced.

66
00:03:38,183 --> 00:03:39,909
O2 saturation is at 93 percent.

67
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:45,150
The EKG looks fine. Could the cause
of the altered consciousness be the brain?

68
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:47,410
No signs of infection either.

69
00:03:50,273 --> 00:03:51,860
There's scleral icterus.

70
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,063
Jaundice.

71
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,463
So it's the liver?

72
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:57,820
Draw blood right away
and check liver function.

73
00:03:57,873 --> 00:03:59,073
Understood.

74
00:04:00,746 --> 00:04:03,706
Dr. Ashura

75
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:10,110
Nothing beats a real bed.

76
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:12,711
Get some rest and focus on getting better.

77
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:14,730
Yeah. I could stay here forever.

78
00:04:15,936 --> 00:04:17,643
- Kuyo, help please.
- Of course.

79
00:04:18,099 --> 00:04:19,337
Coming in.

80
00:04:21,556 --> 00:04:23,196
One, two, three!

81
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:32,730
Mr. Sato? Kenta Sato? Can you hear me?

82
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,240
Yes.

83
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:40,060
What's happening to me?

84
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:44,300
Your liver function declined,
causing a loss of consciousness.

85
00:04:45,053 --> 00:04:49,320
We're running tests now.
We'll update you when results come in.

86
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,573
Understood.

87
00:04:52,487 --> 00:04:53,880
I am counting on you.

88
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:04,786
Chihiro.

89
00:05:06,550 --> 00:05:08,521
I'm sorry for worrying you.

90
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:11,850
Don't be. Just rest for now.

91
00:05:14,630 --> 00:05:18,056
Kenta Sato, age 28, room 3015.

92
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:21,410
Admitted with impaired consciousness
due to liver dysfunction.

93
00:05:21,810 --> 00:05:24,790
AST and ALT are both in the four digits.

94
00:05:25,470 --> 00:05:27,550
Ammonia is high, too. This is pretty severe.

95
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:30,610
Hepatoprotective drugs are helping
for now, but keep a close watch.

96
00:05:30,790 --> 00:05:32,028
Understood.

97
00:05:32,038 --> 00:05:33,456
- Please do.
- Yes.

98
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:39,018
Hey, got a sec?

99
00:05:41,410 --> 00:05:42,790
Sure, go ahead.

100
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,550
The name's Konishi, in the bed next to yours.

101
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:53,823
I'm Sato. Nice to meet you.

102
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:56,810
Tough break, hospitalized so young.

103
00:05:57,510 --> 00:06:01,350
Tell me about it.
I was totally fine until recently.

104
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:05,190
If there's anything I can do,
just say the word.

105
00:06:05,656 --> 00:06:08,990
No, I couldn't. You're a patient, too.

106
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:11,810
Nah, I'm already good. Don't worry about me.

107
00:06:12,530 --> 00:06:14,930
Hey, ending up next
to each other must be fate, right?

108
00:06:16,130 --> 00:06:17,396
Thank you.

109
00:06:17,396 --> 00:06:18,635
Hang in there.

110
00:06:18,690 --> 00:06:21,703
They say laughing boosts your immune system.

111
00:06:21,890 --> 00:06:23,147
Right.

112
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:25,723
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

113
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:27,630
This here's shochu.

114
00:06:47,667 --> 00:06:49,087
That's all you're eating?

115
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:54,120
Yeah. Apparently, protein's no good for me.

116
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:03,500
That ain't enough. Go on,
I haven't touched it yet.

117
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,240
But this is yours.

118
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,120
Nah, don't worry about it. I always eat well.

119
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,803
Thank you.

120
00:07:11,603 --> 00:07:12,632
There we go.

121
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:15,300
Good morning.
Sorry to bother you at breakfast.

122
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,040
You're really energetic this early.

123
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,433
- You're looking better, too.
- Yeah.

124
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:22,700
Mr. Sato, how's your appetite?

125
00:07:23,819 --> 00:07:25,259
Not great.

126
00:07:26,226 --> 00:07:30,440
Your liver function is declining,
so don't force yourself to eat.

127
00:07:31,013 --> 00:07:32,220
Okay.

128
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:39,359
You won't get better if you don't eat. Here.

129
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:42,219
He can't have yogurt either.

130
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:48,710
Well, either way, I can't eat it.
I can't stand yogurt.

131
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:52,729
- You too?
- Huh?

132
00:07:52,729 --> 00:07:56,230
Nah, I hate it too.
I can't handle anything sour.

133
00:07:56,230 --> 00:08:00,210
Tatsu, were you trying to give it away
because you didn't want it?

134
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,519
Busted?

135
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:09,670
I was at that game, you know.

136
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:13,463
What? Seriously? No way, really?

137
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:18,670
Ninth inning, two outs, bases loaded.
I got goosebumps the moment he hit it.

138
00:08:18,710 --> 00:08:22,370
Of course you did. I was listening
on the radio and started crying.

139
00:08:22,416 --> 00:08:26,250
I get it. You really love baseball,
don't you?

140
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:29,030
Yeah, well, it's about the only fun
I got these days.

141
00:08:29,512 --> 00:08:31,330
I've loved it since I was a kid.

142
00:08:31,816 --> 00:08:36,190
So, my dream is to play catch
with my own kid someday.

143
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,610
That sounds great.

144
00:08:40,656 --> 00:08:42,516
It's what I've always wanted.

145
00:08:43,283 --> 00:08:46,796
I never had a father around,
so I never got to do it.

146
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:49,769
I see.

147
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:52,390
That's why I'm gonna beat
this thing for sure.

148
00:08:52,903 --> 00:08:54,159
Yeah.

149
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:59,530
Um, Tatsu, don't you have any family?

150
00:08:59,676 --> 00:09:03,110
Nah. I'm a happy bachelor.

151
00:09:03,130 --> 00:09:04,590
Really? Don't you get lonely?

152
00:09:04,590 --> 00:09:07,296
Lonely? Nah. Freedom is all that matters.

153
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,776
You're a nice guy.
Bet you’re popular with the ladies.

154
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:15,513
Oh, stop it.

155
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,800
What's this?

156
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,630
Picture me when I still had bangs.

157
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,360
Hello! Looks like you're having fun.

158
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,780
We were talking baseball.

159
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,660
Is she your girlfriend?

160
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,560
Yes. We're actually engaged.

161
00:09:33,685 --> 00:09:37,123
Oh, really? I see.

162
00:09:37,211 --> 00:09:40,264
Then you've got to get
better even faster, right?

163
00:09:40,273 --> 00:09:41,484
Right.

164
00:09:42,866 --> 00:09:45,146
The pretty doctor's here.

165
00:09:45,191 --> 00:09:47,391
Up we go. Time to scram.

166
00:09:47,798 --> 00:09:51,258
Mr. Sato, could I have a word with you?

167
00:09:54,612 --> 00:09:56,260
Based on our diagnosis,

168
00:09:57,183 --> 00:10:01,580
your condition is acute liver failure.

169
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:04,320
Is it curable?

170
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:08,003
The cause of this disease is often unclear,

171
00:10:08,698 --> 00:10:13,440
so for now, our plan is to continue treatment
with hepatoprotective drugs.

172
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,220
So the medication will cure it?

173
00:10:17,413 --> 00:10:19,298
There is a chance of recovery.

174
00:10:20,489 --> 00:10:23,860
However, if your condition worsens,

175
00:10:25,145 --> 00:10:28,180
a liver transplant may be necessary.

176
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,277
A transplant?

177
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:39,590
For now, let's focus on treating you
with medication so it doesn't come to that.

178
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:50,436
Even if it comes to a transplant,
Sato has no family, right?

179
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:56,096
His parents divorced over 20 years ago.
He's never been in contact with his father.

180
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:58,543
His mother passed away from illness, too.

181
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:02,410
No siblings either, and apparently
no contact with any relatives.

182
00:11:02,497 --> 00:11:06,287
Then a living donor liver transplant
from a relative seems unlikely.

183
00:11:06,439 --> 00:11:08,115
So if he needs one,

184
00:11:08,163 --> 00:11:12,103
he'd have to hope
for a deceased donor transplant.

185
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:15,910
Surgery did a liver transplant
here recently, right?

186
00:11:16,332 --> 00:11:20,250
Taishaku is a certified liver center,
so we can perform liver transplants.

187
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:28,200
Is my condition really that serious?

188
00:11:31,660 --> 00:11:36,740
The current treatment might work.
Let's stay positive.

189
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,896
Yeah, you're right.

190
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,380
Want to take a walk to clear your head?

191
00:12:00,849 --> 00:12:02,134
Sure.

192
00:12:12,372 --> 00:12:13,582
Are you okay?!

193
00:12:23,106 --> 00:12:25,551
I had no trouble walking yesterday.

194
00:12:29,726 --> 00:12:34,763
Don't push yourself.
I'll get a wheelchair. Okay?

195
00:13:04,868 --> 00:13:07,068
No, this is, uh...

196
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:10,830
How do I put it...
Hospital food just ain't enough.

197
00:13:10,830 --> 00:13:14,990
Cold food strains the stomach.
Not good after food poisoning.

198
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:20,934
Nah, it proves I'm better! Here, look. C'mon.

199
00:13:27,077 --> 00:13:30,460
Oh, what? You're letting it slide?

200
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:34,063
Well, you're being discharged tomorrow.

201
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:45,986
So today's my last day sharing
a room with that young guy.

202
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,670
- Sato?
- Yeah.

203
00:13:49,190 --> 00:13:51,619
So he is...

204
00:13:54,038 --> 00:13:55,440
in pretty bad shape, right?

205
00:13:58,470 --> 00:14:00,483
I can't discuss a patient's condition.

206
00:14:01,823 --> 00:14:03,070
Right.

207
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:17,871
Hey, Doc.

208
00:14:22,529 --> 00:14:24,436
There's something I wanna talk about.

209
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:30,820
It was nice to get some fresh air, right?

210
00:14:31,113 --> 00:14:32,141
Yeah.

211
00:14:32,141 --> 00:14:34,800
Hey, I heard the ER admitted a homeless guy.

212
00:14:34,865 --> 00:14:37,771
Room 301, right? What a nuisance.

213
00:14:37,771 --> 00:14:39,380
They can't pay their medical bills.

214
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:41,705
They're nothing but trouble.
Theft, arguments...

215
00:14:41,705 --> 00:14:42,960
Right.

216
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,503
- Tatsu.
- Huh?

217
00:14:53,749 --> 00:14:54,978
What's wrong?

218
00:14:55,940 --> 00:14:57,168
Nothing.

219
00:14:58,487 --> 00:14:59,753
Okay.

220
00:15:03,283 --> 00:15:05,064
Hey, what's this?

221
00:15:05,751 --> 00:15:11,310
A wheelchair? You feeling that bad?
Is the treatment not working?

222
00:15:15,190 --> 00:15:16,650
They can't really say yet.

223
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:20,161
I see.

224
00:15:20,743 --> 00:15:22,549
Hey, don't worry about it.

225
00:15:22,887 --> 00:15:26,040
Eat well, sleep right, and most
sicknesses just go away on their own.

226
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:27,353
Sorry.

227
00:15:28,217 --> 00:15:31,117
I'm a bit tired.
Mind if I go rest for a while?

228
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:35,167
Sure.

229
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:37,670
Chihiro, sorry. Could you close the curtain?

230
00:15:38,525 --> 00:15:39,730
Sure.

231
00:15:47,697 --> 00:15:50,511
- You must be tired. Want to lie down?
- Yeah.

232
00:15:50,511 --> 00:15:51,758
I'll go get a nurse.

233
00:15:51,856 --> 00:15:53,057
Thanks.

234
00:15:59,620 --> 00:16:03,240
Sato barely touched his dinner.

235
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:08,200
Being put in a wheelchair today must
have been a shock.

236
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:12,480
Acute liver failure really progresses fast...

237
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:16,113
It's a disease
where liver function is lost rapidly.

238
00:16:17,144 --> 00:16:20,972
A patient who seemed
fine yesterday can deteriorate rapidly.

239
00:16:35,679 --> 00:16:38,919
Mr. Sato, time for rounds.
I'm opening the curtain.

240
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,620
Is something wrong?

241
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:46,949
Oh, my wallet's gone missing.

242
00:16:46,949 --> 00:16:48,160
What?

243
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:14,350
What happened?

244
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:19,010
Tatsu, you were over on this side doing
something earlier, weren't you?

245
00:17:22,330 --> 00:17:23,770
I didn't do anything.

246
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:26,610
Really?

247
00:17:30,743 --> 00:17:32,450
Hey, hey!

248
00:17:33,690 --> 00:17:34,896
Found it.

249
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:42,140
Would you care to explain
what's going on here?

250
00:17:45,153 --> 00:17:47,173
It was just a momentary lapse in judgment.

251
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:52,733
I knew it was wrong and was gonna return it.
I didn't take any money!

252
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:02,880
I knew it.

253
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:06,743
I heard the other doctors.

254
00:18:09,330 --> 00:18:12,490
Tatsu, you're homeless, aren't you?

255
00:18:18,116 --> 00:18:22,120
Please move me to another room.
I can't stay with this man.

256
00:18:27,650 --> 00:18:31,050
Why did Tatsu take the wallet?

257
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:33,710
He's not the type to do that.

258
00:18:33,790 --> 00:18:36,510
He didn't touch anything
inside the wallet, right?

259
00:18:36,730 --> 00:18:39,656
Right. He didn't take anything.

260
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:46,850
Any pain?

261
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:48,597
A little.

262
00:18:50,517 --> 00:18:52,676
Did you sleep last night?

263
00:18:53,176 --> 00:18:55,436
Not really.

264
00:18:56,350 --> 00:18:59,610
Yesterday was pretty rough, huh?

265
00:19:00,169 --> 00:19:01,483
Yeah.

266
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:09,350
Um, how's Tatsu doing?

267
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:14,230
He was discharged earlier.

268
00:19:19,370 --> 00:19:20,664
I see.

269
00:19:34,726 --> 00:19:35,973
Hey!

270
00:19:37,213 --> 00:19:38,496
Hey!

271
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:40,068
Who's this?

272
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:41,400
It's me, you idiot.

273
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,817
Tatsu? You got discharged?

274
00:19:44,817 --> 00:19:46,916
Yeah. Back alive, you fool.

275
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:51,780
You're all cleaned up.
I didn't even recognize you.

276
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:55,800
They let me use the bath, then shaved
my beard, too. Look at this handsome mug.

277
00:19:55,806 --> 00:19:59,466
Man, glad you're okay.
We were worried about you.

278
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:02,620
We gotta celebrate!

279
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:06,243
Yeah! Let's live it up for a change.

280
00:20:06,395 --> 00:20:08,728
Right? Yeah, yeah!

281
00:20:09,539 --> 00:20:12,886
We've been treating you
with medication so far,

282
00:20:13,772 --> 00:20:16,362
but we're not seeing sufficient recovery.

283
00:20:18,458 --> 00:20:22,340
A liver transplant will be
necessary after all.

284
00:20:25,753 --> 00:20:27,076
But...

285
00:20:28,327 --> 00:20:31,333
But I don't have any family
who could donate a liver.

286
00:20:31,573 --> 00:20:35,940
We'll register you with the Organ
Transplant Network and wait for a match.

287
00:20:37,087 --> 00:20:38,401
What?

288
00:20:40,058 --> 00:20:42,844
But what do we do in the meantime?

289
00:20:44,854 --> 00:20:47,168
To supplement your liver function,

290
00:20:47,596 --> 00:20:52,990
we'll perform plasma exchange
and continuous hemodiafiltration.

291
00:21:17,646 --> 00:21:19,493
I looked it up...

292
00:21:22,064 --> 00:21:25,425
About 16,000 people are waiting
for a deceased donor transplant.

293
00:21:26,997 --> 00:21:30,570
However, in a year...

294
00:21:33,248 --> 00:21:34,952
Only about...

295
00:21:37,609 --> 00:21:40,763
Six hundred people receive one.

296
00:21:49,487 --> 00:21:50,820
I don't have...

297
00:21:55,527 --> 00:21:57,080
a chance to survive, do I?

298
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:06,940
But you might be chosen.

299
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:09,770
Let's believe.

300
00:22:16,081 --> 00:22:17,309
Kenta?

301
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,524
Kenta, what's wrong? Are you okay?

302
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:23,829
Kenta!

303
00:22:26,549 --> 00:22:28,289
Vegetables are expensive now!

304
00:22:29,757 --> 00:22:31,817
Wait, Tatsu, no alcohol?

305
00:22:32,250 --> 00:22:36,910
Yeah. I quit drinking.
Gotta take care of myself.

306
00:22:37,150 --> 00:22:39,650
At our age, health comes first.

307
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:41,002
Exactly.

308
00:22:41,069 --> 00:22:42,193
Then, should we stop?

309
00:22:42,193 --> 00:22:43,903
- It's fine.
- Hey, hey.

310
00:22:44,483 --> 00:22:46,770
What are you doing? Looks like fun.

311
00:22:47,623 --> 00:22:49,970
Huh? They're having hot pot.

312
00:22:51,123 --> 00:22:53,390
Hey, want some hot pot?

313
00:22:55,376 --> 00:22:57,944
Like hell we would, idiot!

314
00:23:00,687 --> 00:23:02,477
- Is it even edible?
- Don't touch that!

315
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:04,199
Huh?

316
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:07,510
No, please, just leave me alone.

317
00:23:08,078 --> 00:23:09,515
Hey, watch it.

318
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:17,710
Don't mess with me, you punks!

319
00:23:21,536 --> 00:23:22,812
Let go!

320
00:23:29,870 --> 00:23:31,810
You filthy homeless scum!

321
00:23:44,995 --> 00:23:46,476
Crap, is he dead?

322
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,719
Let's go!

323
00:23:58,686 --> 00:24:00,101
Tatsu!

324
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:04,900
Tatsu! Hang in there!

325
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:07,753
Someone! Call an ambulance!

326
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,866
Please!

327
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:12,580
Tatsu!

328
00:24:16,792 --> 00:24:17,925
Blood pressure?

329
00:24:17,925 --> 00:24:19,353
It's 83 over 50.

330
00:24:19,638 --> 00:24:21,134
The gallbladder is swollen.

331
00:24:21,485 --> 00:24:23,360
He's in shock from a gallbladder hemorrhage.

332
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,960
Endoscopy won't stop it.
We need to open him up.

333
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,040
I'll contact the OR.

334
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,264
Yes.

335
00:24:40,090 --> 00:24:43,730
Too much bleeding, I can't get
a clear view. Blood pressure's dropping.

336
00:24:43,950 --> 00:24:46,330
Can't find the bleeding point.
Keep suctioning.

337
00:24:46,430 --> 00:24:47,772
Got it.

338
00:24:51,050 --> 00:24:55,250
Sorry to interrupt. Konishi has been
brought in with a head injury.

339
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:59,530
Dr. Daikoku is treating him,
but he's in very bad shape.

340
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:06,590
The bleeding here won't stop. We keep going.

341
00:25:25,323 --> 00:25:30,130
He was struck on the head and brought in
with cardiopulmonary arrest.

342
00:25:31,931 --> 00:25:35,197
There was no pupillary response
at the time of transport,

343
00:25:35,826 --> 00:25:39,870
and CT showed extensive cerebral edema
extending to the brainstem.

344
00:25:40,903 --> 00:25:43,009
We managed to restore his heartbeat, but...

345
00:25:45,084 --> 00:25:46,570
He won't regain consciousness.

346
00:26:02,121 --> 00:26:03,426
Tatsu...

347
00:26:28,350 --> 00:26:31,723
The surgery was a success.

348
00:26:32,323 --> 00:26:35,540
However, his liver function is
highly unstable.

349
00:26:42,013 --> 00:26:46,720
You may need to prepare for the worst.

350
00:27:23,737 --> 00:27:25,230
This...

351
00:27:26,816 --> 00:27:32,430
Tatsu was holding onto it
like it was incredibly precious.

352
00:27:34,220 --> 00:27:38,256
Figured we should
hand it over to the hospital.

353
00:27:44,103 --> 00:27:47,270
To Dr. Ashura

354
00:27:58,263 --> 00:27:59,503
Anno.

355
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:03,436
There's a way to save Sato.

356
00:28:04,489 --> 00:28:05,690
What?

357
00:28:07,529 --> 00:28:08,796
Because that was...

358
00:28:10,336 --> 00:28:12,349
Tatsu's final wish.

359
00:28:13,603 --> 00:28:15,056
Hey, Doc.

360
00:28:17,616 --> 00:28:20,170
There's something I wanna talk about.

361
00:28:21,603 --> 00:28:24,123
That young guy in the bed next to me...

362
00:28:27,403 --> 00:28:28,816
He's my son.

363
00:28:31,370 --> 00:28:32,696
What do you mean?

364
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:36,203
I knew the moment I saw his face.
No doubt about it.

365
00:28:36,456 --> 00:28:41,790
He's the son I abandoned 24 years ago.

366
00:28:45,110 --> 00:28:50,350
Years ago, I co-signed a friend's loan.

367
00:28:51,483 --> 00:28:55,296
Next thing I knew,
I was stuck with the whole debt.

368
00:28:55,736 --> 00:28:58,330
Then the debt collectors started
showing up at our house.

369
00:28:59,610 --> 00:29:03,763
I knew my wife and kid would be
in danger if I stayed.

370
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:08,450
So I left home.

371
00:29:10,510 --> 00:29:13,590
I basically abandoned them.

372
00:29:15,243 --> 00:29:18,236
Showing up now won't earn his forgiveness.

373
00:29:20,583 --> 00:29:26,090
Hey, Doc.
His condition's pretty bad, isn't it?

374
00:29:26,563 --> 00:29:28,350
Isn't there something we can do?

375
00:29:37,230 --> 00:29:39,370
His liver has almost no function left.

376
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:48,349
If you're his father,
you could donate part of your liver.

377
00:29:58,690 --> 00:30:02,950
I'd do anything for that kid.

378
00:30:06,210 --> 00:30:09,490
But in return, promise me.

379
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:12,450
Promise you'll save him.

380
00:30:12,803 --> 00:30:14,816
Please, Dr. Ashura.

381
00:30:17,390 --> 00:30:18,696
I'm counting on you.

382
00:30:24,170 --> 00:30:27,090
So Tatsu was Sato's father.

383
00:30:27,636 --> 00:30:33,150
He was going to give him his liver
through a living donor transplant.

384
00:30:41,370 --> 00:30:43,510
An organ donor card.

385
00:30:45,063 --> 00:30:46,310
Family priority.

386
00:30:47,329 --> 00:30:49,929
There's also a family register
proving their relationship.

387
00:30:50,990 --> 00:30:54,010
Normally, family consent is required, but...

388
00:30:55,456 --> 00:30:58,390
Since Sato, his only family,
is currently in a coma...

389
00:30:59,476 --> 00:31:01,163
The transplant may be possible.

390
00:31:05,270 --> 00:31:07,750
Contact the organ transplant coordinator!

391
00:31:11,336 --> 00:31:14,089
Organ donation from a deceased donor requires

392
00:31:14,316 --> 00:31:16,276
a strict procedure.

393
00:31:16,955 --> 00:31:19,755
After the transplant coordinator arrives
at the hospital,

394
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:23,570
they verify the donor's condition
and intent to donate.

395
00:31:24,256 --> 00:31:26,590
Two brain death examinations are conducted.

396
00:31:27,970 --> 00:31:34,010
Absence of brainstem reflexes,
flat EEG, no spontaneous breathing...

397
00:31:34,496 --> 00:31:36,690
Once all criteria are met,

398
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:40,596
brain death is legally declared.

399
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:01,510
Dr. Anno.

400
00:32:03,773 --> 00:32:06,460
We're ready for Mr. Konishi's operation.

401
00:32:10,990 --> 00:32:12,196
Understood.

402
00:32:13,710 --> 00:32:18,490
We will now perform a liver transplant
on recipient Kenta Sato.

403
00:32:18,710 --> 00:32:19,790
Understood.

404
00:32:19,790 --> 00:32:20,870
Scalpel.

405
00:32:20,870 --> 00:32:22,070
Here.

406
00:32:39,870 --> 00:32:42,763
Let's have a moment of silence
before we begin.

407
00:33:02,257 --> 00:33:03,656
Tatsu...

408
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:11,340
I'll keep my promise.

409
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:20,976
Let's begin. Scalpel.

410
00:33:21,049 --> 00:33:22,249
Here.

411
00:33:25,656 --> 00:33:26,701
Retractor.

412
00:33:26,701 --> 00:33:27,902
Got it.

413
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:34,636
- Kelly forceps.
- Here.

414
00:33:42,023 --> 00:33:43,110
Pediatric Kelly.

415
00:33:43,110 --> 00:33:44,336
Here.

416
00:33:51,313 --> 00:33:53,133
Cross-clamps. Satinsky.

417
00:33:53,133 --> 00:33:54,446
Here.

418
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:57,000
Stop ventilation.

419
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,923
- Cooper scissors.
- Here.

420
00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:46,576
Liver procurement complete.

421
00:36:05,890 --> 00:36:08,300
The recipient's liver removal is complete.

422
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:12,540
We will now proceed
with the donor liver transplant.

423
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:14,663
Understood.

424
00:37:18,703 --> 00:37:19,929
Kenta.

425
00:37:20,866 --> 00:37:22,413
Kenta, can you hear me?

426
00:37:29,750 --> 00:37:31,610
The transplant was a success.

427
00:37:32,463 --> 00:37:34,163
You're going to be okay.

428
00:37:39,650 --> 00:37:40,989
I see.

429
00:37:47,470 --> 00:37:49,350
Thank goodness.

430
00:37:57,509 --> 00:38:00,220
Mr. Sato, you're awake.

431
00:38:04,217 --> 00:38:06,163
Doctor...

432
00:38:08,163 --> 00:38:13,883
Thank you so much for saving me.

433
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:25,846
Cherish the life you received
from the one who passed away.

434
00:38:30,496 --> 00:38:34,280
Yes, I intend to.

435
00:39:00,090 --> 00:39:01,740
I have something for you.

436
00:39:09,209 --> 00:39:11,103
To Kenta Sato

437
00:39:14,220 --> 00:39:15,526
Who's it from?

438
00:39:17,766 --> 00:39:19,106
Tatsu.

439
00:39:19,806 --> 00:39:22,006
Huh? Tatsu?

440
00:39:26,770 --> 00:39:29,203
He passed away while you were in a coma.

441
00:39:32,486 --> 00:39:33,709
What?

442
00:39:35,257 --> 00:39:36,883
I made a promise.

443
00:39:39,697 --> 00:39:41,430
That I'd save you no matter what.

444
00:40:17,783 --> 00:40:20,550
Dear Kenta Sato.

445
00:40:22,130 --> 00:40:26,390
I should've said this in person,
not in a letter.

446
00:40:27,490 --> 00:40:29,336
But I couldn't find the courage.

447
00:40:30,370 --> 00:40:32,743
Forgive me for being so pathetic.

448
00:40:35,050 --> 00:40:38,616
I agonized over whether
to even write this letter.

449
00:40:39,650 --> 00:40:43,810
I thought maybe disappearing quietly would be
the least I could do to atone.

450
00:40:46,270 --> 00:40:52,329
The moment you were admitted
and I saw your face, I knew you were my son.

451
00:40:58,930 --> 00:41:01,350
At first, I couldn't believe it.

452
00:41:03,163 --> 00:41:06,363
When I tried to look inside your wallet,

453
00:41:06,803 --> 00:41:11,970
it was because I thought I might be wrong
and wanted to check your date of birth.

454
00:41:13,176 --> 00:41:16,743
I'm truly sorry for overstepping like that.

455
00:41:19,790 --> 00:41:25,090
When I learned your life was in danger
and desperately wanted to save you,

456
00:41:25,936 --> 00:41:30,810
Dr. Ashura told me
about a living donor liver transplant.

457
00:41:32,703 --> 00:41:38,910
If there's one thing I can do as a father
who never gave you anything, this is it.

458
00:41:40,710 --> 00:41:45,830
If it means you get to go on living,
my liver is a small price to pay.

459
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:52,080
I'm the worst kind of father.
One who abandoned his family.

460
00:41:52,900 --> 00:41:56,360
I never did a single thing
for you as a father.

461
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:04,460
Not a game of catch, not a baseball game.
Not one single thing.

462
00:42:07,296 --> 00:42:13,416
If you can forgive me,
I'd love to play catch with you.

463
00:42:14,210 --> 00:42:15,986
Take you out for a good meal.

464
00:42:16,923 --> 00:42:21,709
Everything I couldn't do back then,
I want to do it all now.

465
00:42:25,390 --> 00:42:29,390
Kenta, congratulations on your engagement.

466
00:42:30,270 --> 00:42:36,750
Please, from now on, stay healthy
and live a happier life than anyone.

467
00:42:47,530 --> 00:42:48,830
Your father.

468
00:43:17,736 --> 00:43:21,423
Homeless man beaten to death.
Five youths were arrested.

469
00:43:39,626 --> 00:43:40,949
See you.

470
00:43:54,711 --> 00:43:55,736
Next Episode Preview

471
00:43:55,736 --> 00:43:57,580
Time to say goodbye to Yakushiji.

472
00:43:57,580 --> 00:43:58,720
This is the end.

473
00:43:58,720 --> 00:43:59,900
Where am I?

474
00:43:59,900 --> 00:44:01,025
Anno, what's wrong?

475
00:44:01,025 --> 00:44:02,055
I can't see well.

476
00:44:02,055 --> 00:44:03,295
I'm sorry.

477
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:06,160
It's highly difficult
with very few documented cases.

478
00:44:06,220 --> 00:44:08,380
We're just a ragtag bunch.

479
00:44:08,480 --> 00:44:09,760
I can't do this surgery.
